4 L.Ed.2d 1521

Jacob J. GREENWALD
v.
MARYLAND.

No. 920.

Supreme Court of the United States

June 20, 1960

Messrs. Harry Silbert, A. Jerome Diener and Sidney Schlachman, for appellant.

Messrs. C. Ferdinand Sybert, Atty. Gen. of Maryland, Stedman Prescott, Jr., Deputy Atty. Gen., and James H. Norris, Jr. Special Asst. Atty. Gen., for appellee.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a properly presented substantial federal question.
